commit.message: Release 0.8

Add API from libxkbcommon-0.8

Add keysym_to_upper() and keysym_to_lower()

Add missing tests for existing keysym_* functions

Add API from libxkbcommon-0.7

Add ConsumedMode enum, and optional "mode" parameter on
KeyboardState.mod_index_is_consumed() and
KeyboardState.get_consumed_mods()

Add API from libxkbcommon-0.6

Add Keymap.key_get_name() and Keymap.key_by_name()
Release 0.5

Python 3.11 compatibility

enum.IntFlag was changed in a non-backward-compatible manner in Python
3.11. This commit fixes xkb.StateComponent and xkb.StateMatch to retain
the python-3.{6,7,8,9,10} behaviour, and updates the tests to match.
Switch from travis-ci.org to github actions as test runner
Fixes (mostly whitespace) from flake8
Packaging updates / version 0.4
Bump version to 0.3

Fix Context.keymap_new_from_names()

It appears this had never been tested other than with null arguments.

commit.message:
Move ffi_build file

Moving the ffi_build file into the xkbcommon module, which allows the
FFI object to be imported in dependent cffi-based projects.  This is
needed in particular by the pywlroots project to be able to make
xkb_keyboard objects usable in the wlroots API.
